events.description: The Reserve Bank of Australia delivered its first rate hike in two years.

evidences.evidence_text: The central bank lifted rates by 25bps to 3.85%

facts.fact_text: Underlying inflation rose to 3.4% in Q4.

evidences.evidence_text: Underlying inflation rose to 3.4% in Q4, the highest in over a year

claims.claim_text: Stronger-than-expected demand and persistent supply constraints risk keeping inflation elevated.
claims.author: Michele Bullock

evidences.evidence_text: Governor Michele Bullock told lawmakers Friday that stronger-than-expected demand and persistent supply constraints risk keeping inflation elevated.

claims.claim_text: Underlying inflation is projected to peak at 3.7% by mid-year before gradually easing toward target by 2028.

evidences.evidence_text: Underlying inflation rose to 3.4% in Q4, the highest in over a year, and is projected to peak at 3.7% by mid-year before gradually easing toward target by 2028.

evidence.evidence_text: The Reserve Bank of Australia said it must rein in demand growth to restore price stability, after delivering its first rate hike in two years earlier this week.
